Maintainer: Barak A. Pearlmutter <bap@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: raidutils
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Adaptec I2O compliant RAID controller management utilities
 The raidutil programs manage Adaptec I2O-compliant RAID controllers.
 Using them one can create/delete a RAID array, add/remove a hot spare
 drive to/from a RAID array, activate/silence the alarm, and get
 information about the status of the RAID array and disks.
